<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-10T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.35112A/559: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-10T13:00:00-04:00">January
                                    10, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>45. Department would appreciate being advised whether the fact that
                            Italcable closed its doors to the public on December 31 as reported in
                            your No. 17 of January 4 means that the Italian cables which were still
                            being operated by Italcable will no longer be used. Please telegraph as
                            full information as possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>